        %p
          It can be very difficult to tell the difference between diamond color grades. This makes color a flexible trait, and many are perfectly happy with a lower color diamond, especially when you can use the money you save for some extra size or clarity. Of course, having a proper look at some diamonds in person is the best way to find out your feelings on color.
        .panel.callout.radius
          In order to properly evaluate the color of a diamond, gemologists traditionally utilize a set of master stones that represent the standard for each diamond color grade. At GIA, for consistency, the color will be graded by multiple gemologists anonymously and a final color grade is only assigned when there are mutliple graders in agreement.

